dismissalComment.html: An awful mix-up between the wickets! Short midwicket fumbles. Farcical cricket all around. Awful throw. Sarfraz runs in front of the stumps, gathers the throw, flings himself forward, and catches Chandimal short at the striker's end. This was slid through on middle, Chandimal skipped out and clipped it away to shortmidwicket's right, who misfields. Chandimal is more than halfway down the pitch. Thirimanne sells him down the river. Sarfraz made that throw from Shehzad look a lot better

commentPostTextItems.html: 8:48pm And that is the story today. Another Pakistan win. We'll see you for the final ODI on Monday. Good night!

Sarfraz Ahmed: Test cricket is a little different and we have our momentum in this format, we're doing well in all departments. The boys are understanding their roles, especially the seniors. Shoaib bhai stood up with the bat, Hafeez has been doing well in both departments and the young boys are stepping up. They're making my job easy. Whoever is playing is having an impact. These are good signs. [About his batting position] we're not looking to change anything at the moment.

Upul Tharanga: The main thing is batting - we are making the same mistakes. We have a very good batting side so I don't know what is going wrong. I think it has to do with confidence; no one is getting big scores. Hopefully we can do better in the next game. We were 59 for 2 in ten overs and the guys were batting well and after Dinesh [Chandimal] got out, Siriwardana got out early and it was difficult. The spinners have done well but we need to get wickets in the middle overs.

Babar Azam: Praise to God for this award. My focus is always on for every match and I want to give 100%. The longer I'm there, the better it is for both me and the team. The moment Shoaib bhai came in, he said we need to make a partnership and that's what we did.
Babar Azam is the Man of the Match.

8:30pm It seems like the only way Pakistan can lose in this series is if they decide to. And sometimes it looks like they do that. Fifty-eight for 3 at the start of the chase. Makes you wonder what this batting line-up would look like if Babar didn't score for once. But he's that good - he rarely fails in this format. Solid as ever, and aided by the wisdom of Shoaib Malik. They finish unbeaten on the same score, and it's 4-0 to Pakistan. Sri Lanka have lost11 matches in a row. We'll bring you the Man of the Match and the captains soon.
